reviews.productTitle: CLOUDY BAY LED Digital Dimmer Switch for LED Light/CFL/Incandescent, Phrase Cut Dimming 600 Watt max,Cover Plate Included,White,2 Pack
reviews.text: May 22, 2024 - On April 10, 2024, I bought the 2 pack for $19.99. It arrived on time, well packed, and I installed them right away .. Installation was very easy and straight forward. I installed one in a bedroom and one in the guest bathroom.. As some reviews stated, there is a delay on both switches. I did order different light bulbs thinking that maybe I did not have the right bulbs, but no, still same issue, but still, I could live with the delay, no big deal for me. The one in the bedroom still working (for now) delay and all, but over the weekend I discovered that the one in the guest bathroom (that is not used often) is no longer working. I turned the power off, removed the screws and made sure everything was connected ok (it was), but I re-connected the wires and still it did not work. So, I removed the dimmer switch, and installed the old one I previously had. The light is working ok now, but sadly I can't have the dimming capabilities with the old switch. I am guessing I got a defective device that now I can't return because my window to return is over and I do not even have the box it came in. Very upsetting to get $20 down the drain.. I guess it is a hit and miss with these switches, even thou there are many 5 stars, I do not recommend it at all, the old dimmer I have in my dining room still working and that thing is over 25 years old..!
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2024
reviews.title: 2 pack - CLOUDY BAY LED Digital Dimmer Switch for LED Light/CFL/Incandescent,

reviews.productTitle: CLOUDY BAY LED Digital Dimmer Switch for LED Light/CFL/Incandescent, Phrase Cut Dimming 600 Watt max,Cover Plate Included,White,2 Pack
reviews.text: This is an excellent dimmer. I like this type of dimmer design which features a standard size, easy to operate on/off switch in addition a small, narrow dimmer slider - since most of the time I want to turn the light on to a set level. I installed 3 of these in my home and they all work very well. PROS: - I appreciate the short depth (it's less than an inch behind the mounting plate) since my dual-gang switch box has quite a few wires passing thorough it. - Works great on LED-only and LED+incandescent setups. - The small dial for setting the minimum dim level is easily accessible and works well. CONS - The only thing I don't like is that it takes over 1 second to turn the lights on after you hit the switch. I understand that it's better for the bulbs when the voltage level ramps up rather than instantly jumping to 110VAC, but 1+ second is excessive and annoying.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2022
reviews.title: A great dimmer with one annoying issue
